track_notes: Park in the excellent parking area provided graciously by the Estate. Walk up the tarmac road into Killilan. Just before you get to the bridge you can see a building with a prominent construction date (1933) on the front. Turn towards this and pass it to the right (building to your left) right up against the river.  Continue following the obvious track up through the woods and out onto the open hillside. Join the vehicle track and keep left uphill at NG95243054. Continue all the way up the track into the Coire until you reach approx 530M. You can now easily cross all the rivers where they come together.  Climb up steep slopes, tending rightwards until you reach the ridge at approx NG97233012. Follow the ridge easily to the impressively places summit with oddly eroded trigpoint.
track_title: From parking area east of Killilan
